===message:Once again I agree that the underlying problem was that Britain attempted to force their will onto the colonists. Parliment at no time communicated thier actions or the reasoning behind their actions to the colonists they simply went forward (sometimes hurriedly and secretly like with the Townshend Duties) and expected complete obedience.  Britain was used to enforcing their will and thought they could get away with doing the same thing to the colonists.
The colonists were not trying to rock the boat, they only wanted to be represented and treated fairly as evidenced by their continued loyalty to Britain and the crown after the revocation of the Stamp Act in 1766.   
=========yorg=========
